    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.18). **Kyle Tucker** is our primary target against Feltner, benefiting from a massive 14% park boost and a favorable matchup that elevates his base projection significantly. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** holds elite utility as our leadoff man; while the opposition's ability to hold runners slightly dampens his stolen base potential, his position in the order and a strong platoon advantage against the right-handed Williams make him a foundational piece for our Roto output. We are also capitalizing on the high-run environment at Coors Field, where **Josh Lowe** (72.21) and **Nolan Schanuel** (67.16) face Marquez. The matchup against the 5.26 xERA of Marquez is the most favorable on the board, and **Josh Lowe** specifically benefits from a slow-delivering pitcher, which maximizes his elite sprint speed and stealing upside despite a lower spot in the lineup.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Nasim Nunez** (60.21) on the bench. While his score is respectable, he narrowly missed the cut because the density of our current starters\u2014particularly the production we expect from **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and **Jacob Wilson** (70.28)\u2014offered superior efficiency. **Nasim Nunez** offers excellent stolen base potential, but he is currently sidelined by the defensive proficiency of the opposing catcher, which creates a drag on his expected efficiency. We are monitoring the status of **Luis Robert Jr.** (57.07), whose score is suppressed by a difficult platoon split against Taillon; should the lineup shift or weather conditions deteriorate at his venue, we have the flexibility to look at **Heliot Ramos** (52.62) or **Marcell Ozuna** (51.44) as high-floor pivot options. Investors should proceed with caution regarding **Drake Baldwin** (48.67), as his matchup against S\u00e1nchez presents our lowest-scored start of the day; he remains in the lineup to maintain our game cap discipline, but his performance will be the first we monitor for potential late-game defensive replacements.",
